# POC Read-Only — Team Folio Workspace

This rule applies **only in workspaces that include the Team Folio folder**. It does not
affect Ashley's separate POC-only Cursor window, where she keeps full write access.

## The rule

The `upline-poc` folder (at `/Users/ashleyroberts/Documents/upline-poc`) is **reference-only**
from this workspace.

### Never do inside upline-poc:
- Create, edit, or delete files
- `git add`, `git commit`, `git push`, `git pull`
- `git checkout`, `git merge`, `git rebase`, `git reset`
- Run scripts that modify POC files or state

### Allowed (read-only reference):
- Read files
- `git log`, `git branch`, `git show`, `git diff`, `git status` (inspection only)
- Copy content **out** into Team Folio (one-way; never write back)

## Why

Team Folio is a separate venture planning hub. The POC is Austin's codebase and must never
be accidentally changed from this workspace. All Team Folio work happens in the Team Folio
folder and its own git remote.

## Overrides

This rule explicitly overrides any POC workspace rules (e.g. `git-session-end` auto-push)
**while working in this combined workspace**.
